        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): reject surrogate/out-of-range numeric HTML entities",
        "body": "## Problem\nThe Telegram fallback-text entity decoder maps numeric HTML entities via `String.fromCodePoint` without validation. Values in the surrogate range (`0xD800`–`0xDFFF`) or above `0x10FFFF` produce lone surrogates / throw.\n\n## Fix\nReject surrogate-range and out-of-range numeric entities, keeping the original entity text.\n\n## Proof\nAdded a regression in the telegram format test — fails before, passes after. Pure unit test.\n",
